# Smart Waste Management & Bin Level Detection System

## 1. Abstract

The Smart Waste Management & Bin Level Detection System is an IoT-based solution designed to monitor waste bin fill levels in real time. The system uses an HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor to measure the distance between the sensor and the waste surface inside the bin. An ESP32 microcontroller processes the sensor data and calculates the fill percentage. The data is transmitted using the MQTT protocol and visualized on a Node-RED dashboard. Alerts are generated when the bin reaches a predefined threshold, enabling efficient waste collection and preventing overflow.

---

## 2. Introduction

Traditional waste collection systems rely on fixed schedules, often resulting in unnecessary collection trips or overflowing bins. Smart waste management systems use IoT technology to monitor bin status remotely and optimize collection operations.

This project demonstrates how IoT devices, sensors, cloud communication, and dashboards can be integrated to create an intelligent waste monitoring solution.

---

## 3. Problem Statement

Conventional waste collection methods face several challenges:

* Overflowing garbage bins
* Unnecessary collection trips
* Increased fuel consumption
* Higher operational costs
* Poor sanitation conditions

The objective is to develop a system that provides real-time bin monitoring and alerts authorities when waste bins are nearly full.

---

## 4. Objectives

* Measure waste level using an ultrasonic sensor.
* Calculate bin fill percentage.
* Display real-time data on a dashboard.
* Generate alerts when bins are full.
* Improve waste collection efficiency.
* Demonstrate practical IoT implementation.

---

